helpfulAdventurer.flavor: A character who uses her energy to empower rapid click attacks.

A20.flavorText: The Catalog is that area on the bottom left of the UI where you purchase new items.
A20.name: Gem: Buy Random Catalog
A20.tooltip: Automates Buying a Random Catalog Item.

A21.name: Gem: Upgrade Cheapest Item
A21.tooltip: Automates Upgrading the Cheapest Item. It can also purchase a new item, if that is cheaper than all of your upgrades.

A22.name: Gem: Upgrade 3rd Newest Item
A22.tooltip: Automates upgrading the Third Newest Item.

A23.name: Gem: Upgrade 2nd Newest Item
A23.tooltip: Automates upgrading the Second Newest Item.

A25.name: Gem: Upgrade Cheapest Item to x10
A25.tooltip: Automates upgrading the Cheapest Item to the next Multiplier.

A27.name: Gem: Spend All Gold on Cheapest Upgrades
A27.tooltip: Automates spending all gold on Cheapest Upgrades.

A30.name: Stone: World Completions < 1
A30.tooltip: A stone that always activates on the first run of a world.

A36.name: Gem: Next Set
A36.tooltip: Switch to the next Automator Set.

A37.name: Gem: Previous Set
A37.tooltip: Switch to the previous Automator Set.

A38.name: Additional Automator Set
A38.tooltip: Unlocks an additional set for the Automator.

Bc.flavorText: They march loyally behind you in unison, each one prepared to sacrifice itself for your cause.
Bc.name: More Big Clicks
Bc.tooltip: 1 Level of More Big Clicks. Increases the number of clicks empowered by Big Clicks by 1.

Bd.flavorText: They might not look any bigger when you get this upgrade. They're bigger on the inside. In fact, they weigh a lot more.
Bd.name: Bigger Big Clicks
Bd.tooltip: 1 Level of Bigger Big Clicks. Multiplies the damage done by Big Clicks by 125%

Bg.flavorText: When killing monsters, bonus gold may appear. This is a linear bonus, like Crit Chance.
Bg.name: Bonus Gold Chance
Bg.tooltip: 1 Level of Bonus Gold Chance. Adds 1% to your chance of finding bonus gold.

Cc.flavorText: Ever wonder what happens when you get over 100% Crit Chance? The Ancients once knew, but that is ancient history.
Cc.name: Crit Chance
Cc.tooltip: 1 Level of Critical Chance. Adds 2% to your chance to score a critical hit.

Cd.flavorText: When a number is multiplied by a fixed amount (greater than 1) many times, that number is said to grow "exponentially". This is because that process is usually represented by a formula that uses exponential notation.
Cd.name: Crit Damage
Cd.tooltip: 1 Level of Critical Damage. Multiplies the damage of your critical hits by 120%.

Cl.flavorText: This affects damage from all skills that "click". But it does not affect auto-attacks, because those are not "clicks".
Cl.name: Click Damage
Cl.tooltip: 1 Level of Click Damage. Multiplies your click damage by 110%.

Ea.name: Improved Energize
Ea.tooltip: 1 Level of Improved Energize. Increases the duration of Energize by 20% of its original duration.

Eh.flavorText: If a fixed positive amount less than 1 is multiplied to a number many times, that number is said to "approach zero". Enough applications and your number will get very close to, but never actually reach, zero.
Eh.name: Hastened Energize
Eh.tooltip: Multiplies the cooldown and mana cost of Energize by 0.8

En.flavorText: If a fixed amount is added to a number many times, that number is said to grow "linearly". This is because if you plot it out on an x/y graph, you'll see a line.
En.name: Total Energy
En.tooltip: 1 Level of Total Energy. Increases your maximum energy by 25.

G.flavorText: We can also say that it is multiplied by 1.1, but that sounds so much weaker.
G.name: Gold
G.tooltip: 1 Level of Gold Received. Multiplies your gold received from all sources by 110%.

Gb.name: Monster Gold
Gb.tooltip: 1 Level of Monster Gold. Multiplies gold received by monsters by 120%.

Gc.flavorText: If only someone could click on them before they go off the screen.
Gc.name: Clickable Gold
Gc.tooltip: 1 Level of Clickable Gold. Multiplies your gold received from clickables by 150%.

Gp.flavorText: This only affects piles of gold. Not other clickables.
Gp.name: Gold Piles
Gp.tooltip: 1 Level of Gold Piles. Multiplies the number of gold piles found by 110%.

H.flavorText: Haste affects the rate that you auto-attack, and all cooldown speeds, including Automator cooldown speeds.
H.name: Haste
H.tooltip: 1 Level of Haste. Multiplies your Haste by 105%.

Hd.flavorText: It actually gets bigger. But there is an unusual visual side effect that the rest of the world increases in size proportionally.
Hd.name: Huger Huge Click
Hd.tooltip: 1 Level of Huger Huge Clicks. Multiplies the damage done by Huge Click by 125%

I1.name: Equipment: Weapon
I1.tooltip: 1 Level of Weapon Damage. Multiplies the damage you deal with weapons by 150%

I2.name: Equipment: Helmet
I2.tooltip: 1 Level of Helmet Damage. Multiplies the damage you deal with helmets by 150%

I3.name: Equipment: Breastplate
I3.tooltip: 1 Level of Breastplate Damage. Multiplies the damage you deal with breastplates by 150%

I4.name: Equipment: Ring
I4.tooltip: 1 Level of Ring Damage. Multiplies the damage you deal with rings by 150%

I5.flavorText: Pants shouldn't do damage, that's ridiculous.
I5.name: Equipment: Pants
I5.tooltip: 1 Level of Pants Damage. Multiplies the damage you deal with pants by 150%

I6.name: Equipment: Gloves
I6.tooltip: 1 Level of Gloves Damage. Multiplies the damage you deal with gloves by 150%

I7.name: Equipment: Boots
I7.tooltip: 1 Level of Boots Damage. Multiplies the damage you deal with boots by 150%

I8.flavorText: If you wear these in real life, people will think something is wrong with you.
I8.name: Equipment: Cape
I8.tooltip: 1 Level of Cape Damage. Multiplies the damage you deal with capes by 150%

Ir.flavorText: Rufus sometimes wonders why he can't compete in the Gold market. He always felt like there was a mysterious seller undercutting him.
Ir.name: Item Cost Reduction
Ir.tooltip: 1 Level of Item Cost Reduction. Multiplies the gold costs of buying and leveling equipment by 0.92.

Kh.flavorText: If a fixed positive amount less than 1 is multiplied to a number many times, that number is said to "approach zero". Enough applications and your number will get very close to, but never actually reach, zero.
Kh.name: Hastened Clickstorm
Kh.tooltip: Multiplies the cooldown of Clickstorm by 0.8

Md.name: Mana Crit Damage
Md.tooltip: 1 Level of Mana Crit Damage. Multiplies the damage of Mana Crit by 125%

Mo.flavorText: The ancients left some of their greatest powers behind for you to discover.
Mo.name: Mousing over Clickables
Mo.tooltip: Collect Clickables by mousing over them instead of clicking them

Mr.flavorText: You will get 10% more mana per minute than before you had this upgrade.
Mr.name: Mana Regeneration
Mr.tooltip: 1 Level of Mana Regeneration. Multiplies your mana regeneration rate by 110%.

Mt.flavorText: If a fixed amount is added to a number many times, that number is said to grow "linearly". This is because if you plot it out on an x/y graph, you'll see a line.
Mt.name: Total Mana
Mt.tooltip: 1 Level of Total Mana. Increases your maximum mana by 25.

Mu.flavorText: No matter how many of these upgrades you get, MultiClick will take the same amount of time to perform all of its clicks.
Mu.name: Increased MultiClicks
Mu.tooltip: 1 Level of Increased MultiClicks. Adds 2 clicks to your MultiClick.

Pa.name: Improved Powersurge
Pa.tooltip: 1 Level of Improved Powersurge. Multiplies the damage bonus of Powersurge by 125%.

Pc.name: Pierce Chance (NOT IN GAME)
Pc.tooltip: Adds 1% to your chance to hit an additional monster.

Ph.flavorText: If a fixed positive amount less than 1 is multiplied to a number many times, that number is said to "approach zero". Enough applications and your number will get very close to, but never actually reach, zero.
Ph.name: Hastened Powersurge
Ph.tooltip: Multiplies the cooldown and mana cost of Powersurge by 0.8

Pt.name: Sustained Powersurge
Pt.tooltip: 1 Level of Sustained Powersurge. Multiplies the duration of Powersurge by 120%.

Q21.name: Synchrony
Q21.tooltip: Skills do not interrupt Auto Attacks.

Q22.name: Release
Q22.tooltip: Damage is increased by 100% while you have less than 60% of your total energy.

Q23.name: Restraint
Q23.tooltip: Gold gained is increased by 100% while you have more than 40% of your total energy.

Q24.name: Discharge
Q24.tooltip: Spending energy deals damage equal to one click per energy. Consumes Big Clicks and Huge Clicks.

Q25.flavorText: To clarify, this multiplies your haste by 100% plus 1% per point of mana spent in the previous 5 seconds. Gift of Chronos's duration is not decreased by haste.
Q25.name: Gift of Chronos
Q25.tooltip: Spending mana increases haste for 5 seconds.

Q26.name: Curse of the Juggernaut
Q26.tooltip: While Big Clicks is active, all skills cost 1 additional energy per skill that has been activated since Big Clicks began.

Q27.name: Limitless Big Clicks
Q27.tooltip: Big Clicks has no cooldown and can stack infinitely.

Q28.flavorText: This effect can not occur more than once every second.
Q28.name: Jerator's Enchantment
Q28.tooltip: Critical Hits from Auto Attacks can restore 1 mana one time per second.

Q29.flavorText: AutoAttackStorm is like Clickstorm, but does not replace it and can be used in conjunction with Clickstorm.
Q29.name: AutoAttackStorm
Q29.tooltip: Consumes 1.25 mana per second to auto attack 2.5 times per second, until you run out of mana. Speed increases over time.

Q30.name: Managize
Q30.tooltip: Energize becomes Managize, which restores 25% of your mana at the cost of 120 energy over 15 seconds.

Q41.name: Golden Clicks
Q41.tooltip: Consumes 1.25 energy per second to click 2.5 times per second, until you run out of energy. Doubles gold gained while active. Speed increases over time.

Q42.flavorText: Huge Click Discount's duration is not decreased by haste.
Q42.name: Huge Click Discount
Q42.tooltip: Huge Click reduces the cost of items by a portion of your Huge Click's damage bonus for 4 seconds.

Q43.name: Reload Rampage
Q43.tooltip: Reload also returns your current gold to the amount you had at the beginning of the zone, then increases it by Reload's bonus.

Q44.name: Preload
Q44.tooltip: Reload reduces the cooldown of the next skill used by 50%.

Q45.name: Quick Reload
Q45.tooltip: Reload's effects and cooldown are reduced by 80%.

Q61.flavorText: Casting a cooldown-improved Mana Crit will reset the cooldown of your *next* Mana Crit to its original duration.
Q61.name: Bhaal's Rise
Q61.tooltip: Scoring a Critical Hit reduces the remaining cooldown of Mana Crit by 1 second.

Q62.name: Improved Mana Crit
Q62.tooltip: Crit Chance increases the damage of Mana Crit and gives a chance to refund its mana cost, by the amount of Crit Chance you have.

Q63.flavorText: Casting a cooldown-improved Powersurge will reset the cooldown of your *next* Powersurge to its original duration.
Q63.name: Critical Killing Surge
Q63.tooltip: Monsters killed with a Critical Hit reduces the cooldown of Powersurge by 5 seconds.

Q64.flavorText: It will not spill damage over to more than one additional monster.
Q64.name: Mana Crit Overflow
Q64.tooltip: Overkill from Mana Crit damages the next monster.

Q65.name: CritStorm
Q65.tooltip: Consumes 2.5 energy per second to click 5 times per second, until you run out of energy. Clicks from this skill have double chance of being critical strikes. Speed increases over time.

Q66.name: Critical Powersurge
Q66.tooltip: PowerSurge gradually increases Crit Chance while active, reaching +60% at the end of its duration.

Q81.name: Limitless Haste
Q81.tooltip: Removes the 1-second minimum limit on Global Cooldown, allowing Haste to reduce it below 1 second.

Q82.flavorText: Rounded up or rounded down? Only the Ancients know.
Q82.name: Flurry
Q82.tooltip: Haste increases the number of clicks in a MultiClick by the percentage of haste you have.

Q83.flavorText: Killing Frenzy's duration is not decreased by haste.
Q83.name: Killing Frenzy
Q83.tooltip: Multiply your haste by 150% upon killing a monster. Lasts 5 seconds. Does not stack, but the timer will reset with each kill.

Q84.name: Small Clicks
Q84.tooltip: Makes your Big Clicks smaller. Small Clicks are half as strong, but there are twice as many of them.

Q85.name: Expandable Small Clicks
Q85.tooltip: Haste increases the number of charges from Small Clicks, by the percentage of haste you have.

Q86.name: Stormbringer
Q86.tooltip: Small Clicks decreases the remaining cooldown of ClickTorrent by 1 second each.

Q87.name: Hecaton's Echo
Q87.tooltip: Huge Click, when activated, also triggers on every 20th click for the next 100 clicks.

Q88.name: ClickTorrent
Q88.tooltip: Consumes 10 energy per second to click 30 times per second, until you run out of energy. Speed increases over time.

Ra.name: Improved Reload
Ra.tooltip: 1 Level of Improved Reload. Increases the effect of Reload by 50% of its base effect.

Rh.name: Hastened Reload
Rh.tooltip: Multiplies the cooldown of Reload by 0.8

S01.name: Stone: MH more than 50%
S01.tooltip: A stone that can activate when the next monster's health is greater than 50%.

S02.name: Stone: MH less than 50%
S02.tooltip: A stone that can activate when the next monster's health is less than 50%.

S03.name: Stone: Energy more than 90%
S03.tooltip: A stone that can activate when your energy is above 90%.

S04.name: Stone: Energy less than 10%
S04.tooltip: A stone that can activate when your energy is below 10%.

S05.name: Stone: Mana more than 90%
S05.tooltip: A stone that can activate when your mana is above 90%.

S06.name: Stone: Mana less than 10%
S06.tooltip: A stone that can activate when your mana is below 10%.

S07.name: Stone: Zone Start
S07.tooltip: A stone that can activate during the first half of a zone.

S08.name: Stone: Zone Middle
S08.tooltip: A stone that can activate during the second half of a zone.

S09.name: Stone: Boss Zone
S09.tooltip: A stone that can activate during a boss fight.

S10.name: Stone: Crit Chance >= 100%
S10.tooltip: A stone that can activate when your chance to score a critical hit is above 99%.

S11.name: Stone: Energy more than Mana
S11.tooltip: A stone that can activate when your energy is above your mana.

S12.name: Stone: Mana more than Energy
S12.tooltip: A stone that can activate when your mana is above your energy.

S13.name: Stone: Energy less than 40%
S13.tooltip: A stone that can activate when your energy is below 40%.

S14.name: Stone: Energy more than 60%
S14.tooltip: A stone that can activate when your energy is above 60%.

S15.name: Stone: Mana less than 40%
S15.tooltip: A stone that can activate when your mana is below 40%.

S16.name: Stone: Mana more than 60%
S16.tooltip: A stone that can activate when your mana is above 60%.

S17.name: Stone: Before First Zone Kill
S17.tooltip: A stone that can activate before killing the first monster of a zone.

S18.name: Stone: First World Of Gild
S18.tooltip: A stone that can activate when you are on the first world of a gild.

S19.name: Stone: Not First World Of Gild
S19.tooltip: A stone that can activate when you are not on the first world of a gild.

S20.name: Stone: Always
S20.tooltip: A stone that can always activate.

S21.name: Stone: 4s CD
S21.tooltip: A stone that can activate once every 4 seconds.

S22.name: Stone: 8s CD
S22.tooltip: A stone that can activate once every 8 seconds.

S23.name: Stone: 40s CD
S23.tooltip: A stone that can activate once every 40 seconds.

S24.name: Stone: 90s CD
S24.tooltip: A stone that can activate once every 90 seconds.

S25.name: Stone: 10m CD
S25.tooltip: A stone that can activate once every 10 minutes.

S26.name: Stone: Next monster more than 90 cm away
S26.tooltip: A stone that can activate when the next monster is more than 90 cm away.

S27.name: Stone: Not a Boss Zone
S27.tooltip: A stone that can activate when you are not on a boss zone.

S28.name: Stone: Next monster less than 90 cm away
S28.tooltip: A stone that can activate when the next monster is less than 90 cm away.

S51.name: Stone: Clickstorm is not active.
S51.tooltip: A stone that can activate when Clickstorm is not active.

S52.name: Stone: Clickstorm more than 0
S52.tooltip: A stone that can activate when Clickstorm is active.

S53.name: Stone: Autoattackstorm is not active
S53.tooltip: A stone that can activate when Autoattackstorm is not active.

S54.name: Stone: Autoattackstorm is active
S54.tooltip: A stone that can activate when Autoattackstorm is active.

S55.name: Stone: Critstorm is not active
S55.tooltip: A stone that can activate when Critstorm is not active.

S56.name: Stone: Critstorm is active
S56.tooltip: A stone that can activate when Critstorm is active.

S57.name: Stone: Golden Clicks is not active
S57.tooltip: A stone that can activate when Golden Clicks is not active.

S58.name: Stone: Golden Clicks is active
S58.tooltip: A stone that can activate when Golden Clicks is active.

S59.name: Stone: Clicktorrent is not active
S59.tooltip: A stone that can activate when Clicktorrent is not active.

S60.name: Stone: Clicktorrent is active
S60.tooltip: A stone that can activate when Clicktorrent is active.

S61.name: Stone: Energize is not active.
S61.tooltip: A stone that can activate when Energize is not active.

S62.name: Stone: Huge Click is not active.
S62.tooltip: A stone that can activate when Huge Click is not active.

S63.name: Stone: Huge Click more than 0
S63.tooltip: A stone that can activate when Huge Click is active.

S64.name: Stone: Discount is active
S64.tooltip: A stone that can activate when Huge Click Discount is active.

S65.name: Stone: Preload is active
S65.tooltip: A stone that can activate when Preload is active.

S66.name: Stone: Powersurge is not active.
S66.tooltip: A stone that can activate when Powersurge is not active.

S67.name: Stone: Powersurge more than 0
S67.tooltip: A stone that can activate when Powersurge is active.

S68.name: Stone: Big Clicks is not active.
S68.tooltip: A stone that can activate when Big Clicks is not active.

S69.name: Stone: Big Clicks more than 0
S69.tooltip: A stone that can activate when Big Clicks is active.

S70.name: Stone: Big Clicks less than 10
S70.tooltip: A stone that can activate when Big Clicks has less than 10 stacks.

S71.name: Stone: Big Clicks more than 10
S71.tooltip: A stone that can activate when Big Clicks has more than 10 stacks.

S72.name: Stone: Big Clicks less than 50
S72.tooltip: A stone that can activate when Big Clicks has less than 50 stacks.

S73.name: Stone: Big Clicks more than 50
S73.tooltip: A stone that can activate when Big Clicks has more than 50 stacks.

S74.name: Stone: Big Clicks less than 100
S74.tooltip: A stone that can activate when Big Clicks has less than 100 stacks.

S75.name: Stone: Big Clicks more than 100
S75.tooltip: A stone that can activate when Big Clicks has more than 100 stacks.

S76.name: Stone: Big Clicks less than 200
S76.tooltip: A stone that can activate when Big Clicks has less than 200 stacks.

S77.name: Stone: Big Clicks more than 200
S77.tooltip: A stone that can activate when Big Clicks has more than 200 stacks.

S78.tooltip: A stone that can activate when Big Clicks has more stacks than MultiClick can click.

S80.name: Stone: Juggernaut more than 20
S80.tooltip: A stone that can activate when Juggernaut has more than 20 stacks.

S81.tooltip: A stone that can activate when Juggernaut has more than 50 stacks.

S82.tooltip: A stone that can activate when Juggernaut has more than 100 stacks.

S83.tooltip: A stone that can activate when Juggernaut has more than 200 stacks.

S84.name: Stone: Preload is not active
S84.tooltip: A stone that can activate when Preload is not active.

T1.flavorText: When activated, press your mouse button harder for added effect.
T1.name: Skill: Big Clicks
T1.tooltip: Causes your next 6 clicks to deal 300% damage.

T2.flavorText: This skill consumes Mana to create Energy.
T2.name: Skill: Energize.
T2.tooltip: Restores 2 energy per second for 60 seconds.

T4.name: Skill: Clickstorm
T4.tooltip: Consumes 2.5 energy per second to click 5 times per second, until you run out of energy. Speed increases over time.

T5.name: Skill: Huge Click
T5.tooltip: Causes your next click to deal 1000% damage.

T6.name: Skill: Powersurge
T6.tooltip: Causes your clicks within 60 seconds to deal 200% damage.

T7.name: Skill: Mana Crit
T7.tooltip: Clicks with +100% chance to score a critical hit.

T8.name: Skill: Reload
T8.tooltip: Restores energy and mana and reduces the remaining cooldown of all skills by 40%.

Tc.flavorText: Making good use of the lingering powers of a once-loathed ancient known as Thusia.
Tc.name: Treasure Chest Chance
Tc.tooltip: 1 Level of Treasure Chest Chance. Adds 2% to the chance that a monster happens to be a treasure chest.

Tg.name: Treasure Chest Gold
Tg.tooltip: 1 Level of Treasure Chest Gold. Multiplies the gold received from treasure chest monsters by 125%.

Z00.name: Automator Slot
Z00.tooltip: Unlocks an additional slot for the Automator.

qBc.name: Mega More Big Clicks
qBc.tooltip: 3 Levels of More Big Clicks. Increases the number of clicks empowered by Big Clicks by 3.

qBd.name: Mega Bigger Big Clicks
qBd.tooltip: 3 Levels of Bigger Big Clicks. Multiplies the damage done by Big Clicks by 195%

qBg.flavorText: When killing monsters, bonus gold may appear. This is a linear bonus, like Crit Chance.
qBg.name: Fortuna's Luck
qBg.tooltip: 3 Levels of Bonus Gold Chance. Adds 3% to your chance of finding bonus gold.

qCc.name: +20% Crit Chance
qCc.tooltip: This Node does not actually exist in the game.

qCd.name: Precision of Bhaal
qCd.tooltip: 3 Levels of Critical Damage. Multiplies the damage of your critical hits by 172.8%.

qCl.name: The Wrath of Fragsworth
qCl.tooltip: 3 Levels of Click Damage. Multiplies your click damage by 133%.

qEn.name: Juggernaut's Pittance
qEn.tooltip: 4 Levels of Total Energy. Increases your maximum Energy by 100.

qG.name: Mammon's Greed
qG.tooltip: 3 Levels of Gold Received. Multiplies your gold received from all sources by 133%.

qGb.name: Mimzee's Kindness
qGb.tooltip: 3 Levels of Monster Gold. Multiplies gold received by monsters by 172.8%.

qGc.name: Revolc's Blessing
qGc.tooltip: 3 Levels of Clickable Gold. Multiplies your gold received from clickables by 337.5%.

qGp.name: The Vision of Iris
qGp.tooltip: 3 Levels of Gold Piles. Multiplies the number of gold piles found by 130%.

qH.flavorText: Haste affects the rate that you auto-attack, and all cooldown speeds, including Automator cooldown speeds.
qH.name: Vaagur's Impatience
qH.tooltip: 3 Levels of Haste. Multiplies your Haste by 115.7%.

qHd.name: Mega Huger Huge Click
qHd.tooltip: 3 Levels of Huger Huge Click. Multiplies the damage of Huge Click by 195%

qIr.name: The Thrift of Dogcog
qIr.tooltip: 3 Levels of Item Cost Reduction. Reduces the cost of buying and leveling items by 22%.

qMd.name: Mega Mana Crit Damage
qMd.tooltip: 3 Levels of Mana Crit Damage. Multiplies the damage done by Mana Crits by 195%

qMr.name: Energon's Grace
qMr.tooltip: 3 Levels of Mana Regeneration. Multiplies your mana regeneration by 133%.

qMt.name: Energon's Ions
qMt.tooltip: 4 Levels of Total Mana. Increases your maximum Mana by 100.

qMu.name: Mega Increased MultiClicks
qMu.tooltip: 3 Levels of Increased MultiClicks. Adds 6 clicks to your MultiClick.

qTc.name: Mimzee's Favor
qTc.tooltip: 3 Levels of Treasure Chest Chance. Adds 6% to the chance that a monster happens to be a treasure chest.

qTg.name: Mimzee's Blessing
qTg.tooltip: 3 Levels of Treasure Chest Gold. Multiplies your gold received from treasure chests by 195%.
